Let's say I have...
```
case: 'one';
  return 'yes, one';
  break;
```
...and I change it to...
```
case: 'one';
  return 'yes, one';
  break;
case: 'two';
  return 'yes, two';
  break;
```
...then `git diff` will correctly identify the change as...
```
case: 'two';
  return 'yes, two';
  break;
```
...but if I pipe `git diff` to `cdiff`, it shows the change as:
```
  break;
case: 'two';
  return 'yes, two';
```
How can I fix this? Thanks.

pyang 1.7.3 does not appear to support the "modifier" keyword of the pattern statement as documented in YANG 1.1 RFC 7950 section 9.4.6 (https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7950#section-9.4.6).

```
$ pyang --version
pyang 1.7.3

$ pyang -f yang --yang-canonical --lint ...etc..
<...filepath...>.yang:83: error: unexpected keyword "modifier"

# Example YANG code
    79        leaf leaf-name {
    80          type string {
    81            length "1..17";
    82            pattern "(all|none)" {
    83              modifier "invert-match";
    84            }
    85            pattern "[a-zA-Z~@%-_+:|\\[\\]]{1,17}";
    86          }
    87        }
```

Is this a known limitation?

