Both @mgrand (java) and @zballs (go) encountered the same error meanwhile trying to implement code to generate valid transaction payloads.

### Key Pair Generation
BigchainDB relies on the Python cryptoconditions library to generate keypairs, which in turn relies on [libsodium](https://github.com/jedisct1/libsodium) (via [PyNacl](https://github.com/pyca/pynacl)) and [base58](https://github.com/keis/base58).

It is important to note that the base58 library must be an implementation compatible with what is used by the bitcoin network, **but not including the check** (for example, the server uses [`b58encode()`](https://github.com/keis/base58/blob/master/base58.py#L30) rather than [`b58encode_check()`](https://github.com/keis/base58/blob/master/base58.py#L77)). An example Java implementation that should be compatible is available [here](https://github.com/bitcoinj/bitcoinj/blob/master/core/src/main/java/org/bitcoinj/core/Base58.java#L63).

